            <item>
                <title>ggplot2 Theme</title>
                <link>http://aviral.io/articles/ggplot2-theme/</link>
                
                
                <description>&lt;p&gt;I use &lt;a href=&#34;https://ggplot2.tidyverse.org&#34;&gt;ggplot2&lt;/a&gt; nowadays for all my graphing requirements because my research is on improving &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.r-project.org/&#34;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt; and alternatives such as &lt;a href=&#34;https://matplotlib.org/&#34;&gt;matplotlib&lt;/a&gt; are abysmal. This article is a collection of theme settings I have found useful, especially for generating figures for my &lt;a href=&#34;http://aviral.io/publications/on-the-design-implementation-and-use-of-laziness-in-r.pdf&#34;&gt;recent publication on R&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For generating colorless background figures, I use the following theme setting.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-R&#34; data-lang=&#34;R&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;old_theme&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;&amp;lt;-&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;nf&#34;&gt;theme_set&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;nf&#34;&gt;theme_bw&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;()&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;+&lt;/span&gt;
                       &lt;span class=&#34;nf&#34;&gt;theme&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;text&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;nf&#34;&gt;element_text&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;size&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;m&#34;&gt;15&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;),&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;panel.border&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;nf&#34;&gt;element_blank&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;()))&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is how the figures look like before and after updating the theme.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a id=&#34;orgd5774a6&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;




&lt;figure&gt;
    
        &lt;img src=&#34;http://aviral.io/images/ggplot2/without-theme.png&#34; alt=&#34;Figure 1: Figure without updated theme&#34; width=&#34;750px&#34;/&gt; &lt;figcaption&gt;
                
                &lt;p&gt;
                    Figure 1: Figure without updated theme
                    
                        
                        &lt;/p&gt;
                
            &lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;


&lt;p&gt;&lt;a id=&#34;org3ee6670&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;




&lt;figure&gt;
    
        &lt;img src=&#34;http://aviral.io/images/ggplot2/with-theme.png&#34; alt=&#34;Figure 2: Figure with updated theme&#34; width=&#34;750px&#34;/&gt; &lt;figcaption&gt;
                
                &lt;p&gt;
                    Figure 2: Figure with updated theme
                    
                        
                        &lt;/p&gt;
                
            &lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;


&lt;p&gt;These figures were generated from the following code snippet.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-R&#34; data-lang=&#34;R&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;nf&#34;&gt;library&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;ggplot2&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;

&lt;span class=&#34;nf&#34;&gt;ggplot&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;mpg&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;nf&#34;&gt;aes&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;class&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;))&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;+&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class=&#34;nf&#34;&gt;geom_bar&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;()&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
                
